      </statement>
      <choices randomize="yes">
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>7.0 \times 10^{-6}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>Your digital blade missed the mark, try again.  <m>7.0</m> is missing something.</p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>7.02 \times 10^{6}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>While the decimal moved 6, it was moved to the right which results in a negative power of 10.</p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="yes">
          <statement><p><m>7.02 \times 10^{-6}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>Correct! <m>0.00000702 = 7.02 \times 10^{-6}</m></p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>7.02 \times 10^{-5}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>Your enchanted click missed the mark, try again. That's <m>0.0000702</m>, not <m>0.00000702</m>.</p></feedback>
        </choice>
      </choices>
    </exercise>
    <!-- Prep q03 -->
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>Convert <m>0.70</m> to scientific notation.</p>
      </statement>
      <choices randomize="yes">
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>0.70 \times 10^{0}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>While this is true, <m>0.70</m> is less than <m>1</m>. So this is not considered scientific notation.</p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>7.0 \times 10^{1}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>While the decimal moved one, it was moved to the right which results in a negative power of 10.</p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="yes">
          <statement><p><m>7.0 \times 10^{-1}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>Correct! <m>0.70 = 7.0 \times 10^{-1}</m></p></feedback>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="no">
          <statement><p><m>0.70 \times 10^{1}</m></p></statement>
          <feedback><p>Your digital blade missed the mark, try again. That's <m>7.0</m>, not <m>0.70</m>. Also, <m>0.70</m> is less than <m>1</m></p></feedback>
        </choice>
      </choices>
    </exercise>
